author: Home Repair Tutor
description: Plywood subfloor removal tips…Oscillating multi-tools are great for cutting plywood close to walls. I’m removing this 1/2 inch plywood because it’s not thick enough for the shower tray and tile floors. I always use 3/4 inch (23/32) which is excellent over 16 inch on-center floor joists. If you’re looking for super detailed tutorials visit me at homerepairtutor.com 🔥#bathroomremodel #homerenovation #showerremodel #diy #homerepairtutor
